ðŸ§© Problem Solved: Leetcode 215. Kth Largest Element in an Array (Medium)
ðŸ”— Problem Link: https://lnkd.in/dJebJ3rD

class Solution {
public:
    int findKthLargest(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        // Get the number of elements in the vector
        int n = nums.size();

        // Sort the vector in ascending order (e.g., using quicksort or mergesort)
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());

        // Return the kth largest element, which is at the (n - k)th position in the sorted array
        return nums[n - k];
    }
};

The dominant factor in this function is the sorting step using sort. The average time complexity of sorting an array with N elements using a comparison-based sorting algorithm like quicksort or mergesort is O(N * log(N)).
